{"title_page": "2009 flu pandemic table October 2009", "text_new": "{{Further|2009 swine flu pandemic by country}}\n{{See also|2009 swine flu pandemic timeline}}\n{{Main article|2009 swine flu pandemic}}\n\nThis is a table containing the figures from the [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control|ECDC]] Influenza A Situation Updates issued in October 2009 roughly three times a week.<ref>[http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/Health%5Ftopics/novel%5Finfluenza%5Fvirus/2009%5FOutbreak/ ECDC Situation Reports]  {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090805215435/http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/Health_topics/novel_influenza_virus/2009_Outbreak/ |date=August 5, 2009 }}</ref>  From 30 September, ECDC only published deaths totals, and so the world cases table has not been maintained. The table can be sorted by country, date of first confirmed case or date of first confirmed case by continent.\n\nThis presentation of the data in this and other tables may show the progression, peaks, and, eventually, decline of the epidemic in each country and continent.\n\n[[2009 flu pandemic tables|Summary tables]] | [[2009 flu pandemic table September 2009|Previous month]] | [[2009 flu pandemic table November 2009|Next month]]\n\n==Deaths==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" align=\"center\"\n|+'''Swine flu deaths, October 2009'''\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|By date\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|By cont.\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|Country or territory\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|2\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|5\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|7\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|9\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|12\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|14\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|16\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|19\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|21\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|23\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|26\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|28\n! style=\"background:#874bd1\"|30\n|-\n| 0 || 0 || {{noflag}}''World'' || 4433 || 4495 || 4525 || 4579 || 4675 || 