{"title_page": "2009 flu pandemic table July 2009", "text_new": "{{Further|2009 swine flu pandemic by country}}\n{{See also|2009 swine flu pandemic timeline}}\n{{Main|2009 swine flu pandemic}}\n\nThis is a table containing the figures from the [[World Health Organization|WHO]] Influenza A Situation Updates issued in July 2009 roughly three times a week,<ref>[http://www.who.int/csr/disease/swineflu/updates/en/index.html WHO Situation Updates]</ref> and, since 15 July, figures from [[European Centre for Disease Prevention and Control|ECDC]].  The table can by sorted by country, date of first confirmed case or date of first confirmed case by continent.\n\nThis presentation of the data in this and other tables may show the progression, peaks, and, eventually, decline of the epidemic in each country and continent.\n\nNote that no global report has been issued by WHO since 6 July - the data on 8 July was compiled from the reports of each of WHO's six regions,<ref>[http://www.afro.who.int/ African region]</ref><ref>[http://new.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_content&task=blogcategory&id=805&Itemid=569 Region of the Americas] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708200156/http://new.paho.org/hq/index.php?option=com_content&task=blogcategory&id=805&Itemid=569 |date=July 8, 2009 }}</ref><ref>[http://www.emro.who.int/csr/h1n1/ Eastern Mediterranean region]</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.euro.who.int/influenza/ah1n1 |title=European region |access-date=2009-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090708231900/http://www.euro.who.int/influenza/ah1n1 |archive-date=2009-07-08 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.searo.who.int/EN/Section10/Section2562.htm |title=South-East Asia region |access-date=2009-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090709192245/http://www.searo.who.int/EN/Section10/Section2562.htm |archive-date=2009-07-09 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.wpro.who.int/health_topics/h1n1/ |title=Western Pacific region |access-date=2009-07-09 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090716192240/http://www.wpro.who.int/health_topics/h1n1/ |archive-date=2009-07-16 |url-status=dead }}</ref> and since 15 July has been taken from ECDC.<ref>[http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/Health_topics/novel_influenza_virus/2009_Outbreak/ ECDC data] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090716071147/http://www.ecdc.europa.eu/en/Health_topics/novel_influenza_virus/2009_Outbreak/ |date=July 16, 2009 }}</ref>\n\n[[2009 flu pandemic tables|Summary tables]] | [[2009 flu pandemic table June 2009|Previous month]] | [[2009 flu pandemic table August 2009|Next month]]\n\n==Confirmed cases==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" align=\"center\"\n|+'''Swine flu cases, July 2009'''\n! By date\n! By cont.\n! Country or territory\n! 1 !! 3 !! 6 !! 8 !! 15 !! 16 !! 17 !! 20 !! 22 !! 24 !! 27 !! 29 !! 31\n|-\n| 0 || 0 || {{noflag}} ''[[World]]'' || 77201 || 89921 || 94512 || 101922 || 125993 || 128325 || 130727 || 141962 || 164541 || 159294 || 163859 || 175769 || 183590\n|-\n| 0 || 0 || Days to double (approx) || 15 || 14 || 16 || 18 || 20 || 19 || 19 || 19 || 20 || 21 || 22 || 24 || 25\n|-\n| 0 || 0 || Countries || 121 || 126 || 136 || 139 || 146 || 149 || 150 || 152 || 155 || 155 || 157 || 162 || 165\n|-\n| 1 || 1.01 || {{flag|Mexico}} || 8680 || 10262 || 10262 || 11271 || 12645 || 12645 || 12645 || 13646 || 14229 || 14861 || 15383 || 16019 || 16442\n|-\n| 2 || 1.02 || {{flag|United States of America}} || 27717 || 33902 || 33902 || 33902 || 37246 || 37246 || 37246 || 40617 || 40617 || 43771 || 43771 || 43771 || 43771\n|-\n| 3 || 1.03 || {{flag|Canada}} || 7983 || 7983 || 7983 || 9066 || 985 || 10156 || 10156 || 10156 || 10156 || 10156 || 10156 || 10449 || 10449\n|-\n| 16 || 1.04 || {{flag|Costa Rica}} || 279 || 227 || 277 || 277 || 428 || 428 || 428 || 428 || 560 || 560 || 606 || 606 || 668\n|-\n| 19 || 1.05 || {{flag|El Salvador}} || 226 || 253 || 319 || 319 || 404 || 404 || 404 || 