n]] (now at [[The View (talk show)|''The View'']])\n* [[Bill McCuddy]]\n* [[Zell Miller]]\n* [[Maria Molina]]\n* [[Clayton Morris]]\n* [[Dick Morris]] (contributor, not renewed)\n* [[Heather Nauert]] (now Senior Fellow at the [[Hudson Institute]])\n* [[Scottie Nell Hughes]] (terminated)\n* [[Joanne Nosuchinsky]]\n* [[Robert Novak]] (deceased)\n* [[Bill O'Reilly (political commentator)|Bill O'Reilly]] (terminated amid sexual harassment allegations)\n* [[Barbara Olson]] (killed in the [[September 11 attacks]] in 2001)\n* [[Morgan Ortagus]] (now U.S. State Department Spokesperson)\n* Lt. Col. [[Ralph Peters]]\n* [[Uma Pemmaraju]]\n* [[Julian Phillips]]\n* [[Kirsten Powers]] (now at CNN)\n* [[Elizabeth Prann]]\n* [[Judith Regan]]\n* [[Julie Roginsky]]\n* [[Ed Rollins]] (not renewed)\n* [[James Rosen (journalist)|James Rosen]]\n* [[Rick Santorum]] (now with CNN)\n* [[Mike Schneider (news anchor)|Mike Schneider]] (left for [[Bloomberg Television]], most recently at [[NJTV]])\n* [[Laura Schwartz]]\n* [[Bob Sellers]] (now morning co-anchor at [[WZTV]] in Nashville)\n* [[Suzanne Sena]]\n* [[David Shuster]] (now at i24NEWS)\n* [[Jane Skinner]]\n* [[Shepard Smith]] (resigned)\n* [[Tony Snow]] (became [[White House Press Secretary]], deceased)\n* [[John Stossel]]\n* [[Andrea Tantaros]]\n* [[Cal Thomas]] (not renewed)\n* [[Greta Van Susteren]] (left for MSNBC, now at [[Gray Television]])\n* [[Linda Vester]]\n* [[George Will]] (now at NBC News and MSNBC)\n* [[Brian Wilson]] (presently morning drive time host on [[WMAL-FM]])\n* [[Paula Zahn]] (left for CNN, now at [[Investigation Discovery]]){{div col end}}\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|New York City|Companies|Television|United States}}\n* [[Alternative facts]]\n* [[The Fox Nation (website)|The Fox Nation]]\n* [[Fox effect|Fox Effect]]\n* [[Fox Music]]\n* [[Fox News Radio]]\n* [[Sun News Network]] - a short-lived Canadian attempt at creating a similar news channel for conservative Canadian viewers\n{{Clear}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Refbegin}}\n* {{cite book |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-Xj7CwAAQBAJ&pg=PP1 |title=Fox News and American Politics: How One Channel Shapes American Politics and Society |last=Cassino |first=Dan |publisher=Routledge |year=2016 |isbn=978-1-317-47999-4}}\n* {{Cite journal |last1=Hopkins |first1=Daniel J. |last2=Ladd |first2=Jonathan M. |title=The consequences of broader media choice: evidence from the expansion of Fox News |journal=[[Quarterly Journal of Political Science]] |volume=9 |issue=1 |pages=115\u2013135 |doi=10.1561/100.00012099 |date=March 2014 |ref=harv }}\n{{Refend}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Fox News Channel}}\n* {{official website}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{White House James S. Brady Press Briefing Room Seating Chart}}\n{{Television news in the United States}}\n{{FoxNewsChannelPrograms}}\n{{Fox News personalities}}\n{{Fox (company)}}\n{{Sirius XM Channels}}\n{{Television news in Australia}}\n{{Subscription television channels in Australia}}\n{{Channels on Sky Network Television}}\n}}\n\n[[Category:24-hour television news channels in the United States]]\n[[Category:English-language television stations in the United States]]\n[[Category:Foreign television channels broadcasting in the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Fox News|*]]\n[[Category:Fox Corporation subsidiaries]]\n[[Category:Sirius Satellite Radio channels]]\n[[Category:Television channels and stations established in 1996]]\n[[Category:XM Satellite Radio channels]]\n[[Category:Conservative media in the United States]]\n[[Category:1996 establishments in the United States]]\n", "text_old": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{other uses}}\n{{short description|American conservative television news channel}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2020}}<!--- WARNING: Please Adhere to Wikipedia' Neutral Point of View policy; any uncited controversies will be reverted!--->\n{{Infobox television channel\n| name = Fox News\n| logofile = Fox News Channel logo.svg\n| logosiz